raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "westpa" %}
{% set version = "2022.02" %}
{% set sha256 = "a40a4110031e1bc5b0d336f39886cdf6c617e19c52a7914ef6f2e3fd2731ebf0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://github.com/westpa/{{ name }}/archive/refs/tags/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [win or py2k]
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps"

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cython >=0.29.16                       # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy >=1.16                           # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - setuptools >=40.8.0
    - python
    - wheel
    - cython >=0.29.16
    - numpy >=1.16
    - scipy >=0.19.1
    - versioneer-518
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - scipy >=0.19.1
    - h5py >=2.10
    - mdtraj >=1.9.5
    - pyyaml >=5.3.*
    - pyzmq >=19.0.*
    - matplotlib-base
    - blessings 1.7.*
    - ipykernel
    - tqdm
    - pandas
    - pytables

test:
  imports:
    - westpa
    - westpa.core.propagators
    - westpa.core.binning
    - westpa.core.kinetics
    - westpa.core.reweight
    - westpa.work_managers
    - westpa.tools
    - westpa.fasthist
    - westpa.mclib
    # Currently blocked by https://github.com/westpa/westpa/issues/70
    #- westpa.trajtree
    # Skipping the following so it'll pass on macs 
    #source_files:
    #- tests/*.py
    #- tests/test_tools
    #- tests/refs
    #- tests/fixtures
    #requires:
    #- pytest
    #- nose
    #commands:
    #- pytest -v tests/

about:
  home: https://westpa.github.io/westpa
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Interoperable, highly-scalable software for weighted ensemble simulation.'

  description: |
    WESTPA is a package for constructing and running stochastic simulations
    using the "weighted ensemble" approach of Huber and Kim (1996).
  doc_url: https://westpa.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/westpa

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mczwier
    - synapticarbors
    - burntyellow
    - ltchong
    - jeremyleung521
